tsdb.util.iterator

Class MoveIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • tsdb.util.iterator.TsIterator
      • tsdb.util.iterator.MoveIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<TsEntry>, ProcessingChainEntry, ProcessingChainNode, ProcessingChainSupplier
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AverageIterator, EvaluatingAggregationIterator, InputProcessingIterator, MergeIterator, MiddleIterator, MinDiffIterator, TsIteratorIterator

    public abstract class MoveIterator
extends TsIterator
    Time series iterator that stores the current element.

    This iterator my simplify processing iterators.
    Extending classes need to implement getNext() only.

      • getNext

        protected abstract TsEntry getNext()
        Request next element.

        It's guaranteed to not be called again when it first returns null (no next element).
        This method should be called by MoveIterator internal only.

        Returns:
        next element or null if there is no next element

      • close

        public void close()
        Signals that iterator does not contain a next element.
        So getNext() will not be called again.
